<%= render 'head' %>
<body>
<%= render 'header' %>
<div class="container-fluid" style="height:1000px">

    <%= render 'sidebar' %>

    <div class="col-md-8 text-justify">
      <h1 style="font-size: 4em;">Specifications</h1>
      <!-- could add list group with drop down that appears and disappears
           use the bookmarked jsfiddle :) -->
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Scientifically accurate:</strong> both common and scientific names including the author(s) for each plant and all known common and scientific name synonyms for each species.</li>
        <li><strong>Text based:</strong> using carefully selected common terms of form and structure for identification with drawings and photographs to help confirm identifications.</li>
        <li><strong>Jargon Free:</strong> keeping technical terms to an absolute minimum, but with full definitions of any term available with a single tap.</li>
        <li><strong>Pocketable:</strong> fitting into just about any sized pocket makes the smartphone ideal for this purpose. You won't have to take bulky and heavy field guides with you. Since a smartphone is usually carried at all times you won't have to remember to take it.</li>
        <li><strong>Intuitive:</strong> easy to use and understand. You'll rarely need to consult the help menu.</li>
        <li><strong>Web-Independent:</strong> providing plant identification without an active Internet or wireless connection.</li>
        <li><strong>Searchable:</strong> providing lists of both common and scientific names of plants including synonyms and other names.</li>
        <li><strong>Updateable:</strong> adding new data periodically as it is developed.</li>
        <li><strong>Free:</strong> fully functional application to be available to any end-user.</li>
        <li><strong>Multiple platform:</strong> will function on a variety of smartphone platforms.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<%= render 'footer' %>
</body>
